-- Japanese Bought Net 474.6 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   D a n i e l   P e t r i e
-- 2012-10-24T23:56:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-24/japanese-bought-net-474-6-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Oct. 19 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 474.6 billion yen ($5.9 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 0.9 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 81.6 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 555.3 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 272.3 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 195.2 billion yen in stocks, and sold 165.6 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 302
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
